  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  Translator: Burton Watson
Title: Discussion On Making All Things Equal
---
TZU-CH'I OF SOUTH WALL sat leaning on his armrest, staring up at the
sky and breathing - vacant and far away, as though he'd lost his
companion. Yen Ch'eng Tzu-yu, who was standing by his side in
attendance, said, "What is this? Can you really make the body like a
withered tree and the mind like dead ashes? The man leaning on the
armrest now is not the one who leaned on it before!"
